      "text": [
        " : سَأَلْتُهُ عَنِ اَلْمُحْرِمِ إِذَا اِحْتَاجَ إِلَى ضُرُوبٍ مِنَ اَلثِّيَابِ مُخْتَلِفَةٍ فَقَالَ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ «عَلَيْهِ لِكُلِّ صِنْفٍ مِنْهَا فِدَاءٌ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.2623 - Muhammad ibn Muslim narrated from one of the Imams (as), who said:\nI asked him about a Muhrim who needs to wear various types of different clothing.\nImam (as) said: \"For each type of clothing, he must offer an expiation (fidya).\""
        ]
      }
